race.comment: A small but even field remains after most of the key runners were scratched. The one with the right credentials is SHYLOCK (7) who led all the way to win a similar race here three weeks ago. Should get a nice sit behind the leader and will be hard to hold out again. FINAL IMPACT (5) gave away a big start but went through his gears nicely in the closing stages to be beaten just over two lengths in a 2150m BM58 at Gunnedah last time out. Will settle far closer in this small field and he is a threat. TAVIJEWEL (9) was runner-up two back over 2100m at Orange then curiously went back to 1375m most recently in a run worth overlooking. Likely leader who can give plenty of cheek. JOSHUA (10) goes around every week and picks up small cheques for connections. Should be about the mark. WILL TO EXCEL (1) has his share of weight but is good enough to figure in the finish.
